<div class="drizzle-o-Layout-content drizzle-b-LongFormText">
  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <p>Our design principles are shared guidelines that capture the essence of what good design means our company and
      advice on how to achieve it.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <h2 class="drizzle-b-h2">Clarity</h2>
    <p>Help eliminate ambiguity and enable users to see, understand and act with confidence. Keep the user focused on
      their goal without distraction.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <h2 class="drizzle-b-h2">Consistency</h2>
    <p>Create familiarity & strengthen intuition by applying the same solution to the same problem. Use consistent
      language, patterns and components across the experience to make it easier for clients to get stuff done..</p>
  </div>
  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <h2 class="drizzle-b-h2">Beauty</h2>
    <p>Every aesthetic design decision - from how we design components, to illustrations, and choices about color -
      should be purposeful. Build trust and further imbue confidence with an experience that appears and interacts
      beautifully.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <h2 class="drizzle-b-h2">Inclusive</h2>
    <p>Be inclusive, legible and as readable as possible across the experience. Thoughtfully serve the needs of all
